[ti:The Choice]
[ar:Xauz Khuangz]
[00:14.50]They say, “I had no choice,” but I know that isn’t true,
[00:27.20]Even standing in the dark is something we all choose.
[00:40.00]Bread upon the table, hunger in my chest,
[00:53.00]I eat not out of force, but knowing what comes next.
[01:06.00]I always had a choice, even when it hurt,
[01:19.00]Even when my heart chased fire, knowing I’d get burned.
[01:31.50]It’s not the lack of options, it’s the price we try to avoid,
[01:44.80]Every path asks something—yes, I always had a choice.
[02:03.50]Happiness isn’t waiting, it’s built with honest pain,
[02:17.00]It’s choosing to keep walking in the wind and in the rain.
[02:30.00]So don’t say you were powerless, don’t silence your own voice,
[02:37.00]Life is shaped by moments where we choose…
[02:41.50]You always had a choice.
[02:43.00]I always had a choice, even when it hurt,
[02:56.50]Even when my heart chased fire, knowing I’d get burned.
[03:09.50]It’s not the lack of options, it’s the price we try to avoid,
[03:22.50]Every path asks something—yes, I always had a choice.